The percentage of engaged households purchasing an item as a percentage of engaged households that shop in the whole store.  This is calculated for the stores in the selection.  Note this metric is valid at any level of aggregation of store and product, e.g. brand by cluster.

The Loyalty Score is also known as the Preferred Item Score in other systems. Assort uses the Preferred Item Score to identify product loyalty and further derive product incrementality. The process by which the Preferred Item Score is calculated is as follows: Step 1. Within a product universe calculate the total number of units a household purchases Step 2. For each household and product calculate the proportion of product universe units each individual unit accounts for Step 3. Flag an item as preferred if: The households total purchase in the universe is >=3 The households proportion of purchase on the item is >0.33 Step 4. Calculate for all items the amount of units to preferred customers and those in total Step 5. Preferred item score is preferred units / total units Note when viewing the Loyalty Score at different levels of store aggregate the score will only be calculated from the level you are looking at if there are at least 500 carded units. If there are less than 500 carded units the score will be calculated from a more aggregate level, i.e. CLUSTER, MODEL CLUSTER (if defined) or SUPER CLUSTER, depending on where the 500 unit threshold is reached. If the threshold is not reached the value will be calculated at the SUPER CLUSTER level.

The sales (in cash) generated for the given product (or product group) in the total market (all retailers). Note that this number does not change depending on the level of retailer aggregation at which you are viewing it, i.e. you will see the same values if you view at Banner or Cluster.

The sales (in units generated for the given product (or product group) in the total market (all retailers). Note that this number does not change depending on the level of retailer aggregation at which you are viewing it, i.e. you will see the same values if you view at Banner or Cluster.
